&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Nurse &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Team - Melsham and BOA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Melksham and Bradford on Avon Community Team is passionate about nursing, zealous about helping to keep people in their own homes and enthusiastic about supporting each other.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We vehemently try to prevent patients from being admitted to hospital unnecessarily and support people at the end of their life to stay at home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We currently need a qualified Band 5 nurse to work full time in our team (5 x 7.5 hour shifts).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are responsive to training needs, offer support, mentorship and teaching to become skilled in caring for the complex patients we now have on our caseloads.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our community nurses work in patient’s homes, in community clinic and link closely with the GP practices in Melksham and Bradford on Avon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have up to date clinical skills, good communication skills, motivation, and enthusiasm and are hardworking then come and join us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a busy friendly team who would welcome new or experienced members of staff who would be willing to contribute to the on-going development of the community service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested, please see the advertisement on NHS Jobs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can also contact us directly for an informal chat.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kate Payne or Donna Pearce.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team Lead at Melksham and Bradford on Avon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01225 701051.&lt;/p&gt;
